{
  "texts": [
    "The selectivity is a key requirement to minimize the extent of outages during fault events and it is an area where traditional protection struggles due to use of simple decision functions with a limited set of inputs.",
    "Machine learning that can be effectively used to improve the selectivity of difficult protection problems by recognizing patterns and complex scenarios.",
    "In power system protection, rapid fault isolation is desirable, but achieving very high-speed operation can lead to undesired actions.",
    "Time remains a reliable means of distinguishing tolerable from intolerable transients.",
    "It is desirable for a protection relay to operate as soon as a fault is correctly detected."
  ]
}